Then Sir Thomas Stringer, Serjeant at Law of Counſel
with the King in this Cauſe, opened the Indictment
thus;

sp.p:
                  Le Faire and VVelſh. The next Morning.


                  Le Faire came to my Chamber, and I was not then within;
but by Accident I met him, about four of the Clock
in Lincolnes-Inn-Fields. We went to the Palſgraves Head Tavern;
where falling into Diſcourſe, he told me there vvas
a Gentleman that vvas to be put out of the vvay; that
vvas the Phraſe he uſed, he did not really ſay Murther him;
for they don't count it Murther.

Then we deſire to call the Chyrurgeons that
view'd and opened the Body, Mr. Skillard, and Mr. Cambridge;
both whom were Sworn.

Here is a great Circumſtance my Lord. I asked
her what Clothes he was in when he came to Sir Edmondbury's;
and ſhe ſaith, the ſame that he hath now.

Do you remember you were ſent of a meſſage
from the Queens-Head at Bow, and whether? Pray tell my Lord,
and the Jury.

Yes, I can, becauſe I ſaw him come in conſtantly;
and when he came in, I always ſent my Maid to bar the
door.

You told me juſt now you were not upon Confeſſion;
and I tell you now ſo, you are not. Then Mrs. Broadſtreet
was examined.
